     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To his deare Friend M<seg rend="sup">r</seg> FULLER.</head>
   <l>WE need not now those zealous vot'ries meet,</l>
   <l>Or pilgrimes turn; but on our verses feet.</l>
   <l>Thy quill hath wing'd the earth; the Holy land</l>
   <l>Doth visit us, commanded by thy hand.</l>
   <l>If envy make thy labours prove thy losse,</l>
   <l>No marvel, if a <hi>Croisade</hi> wear the Crosse.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>CLEMENT BRETTON, Sidn. Coll.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
